(
<figureCitation id="41D52A05280EFFA7FF14FA5CFEE3FA05" box="[159,294,1411,1438]" captionStart="FIGURES 61–66" captionStartId="32.[151,264,1849,1873]" captionTargetBox="[164,1425,192,1803]" captionTargetId="figure-21@32.[151,1436,181,1825]" captionTargetPageId="32" captionText="FIGURES 61–66. Bezzia marylandensis n. sp. Male, 61–63, Female, 64–66. 61 Head. 62 Thorax and legs. 63 Genitalia at focal level of sternite 9, parameres, aedeagus, gonocoxites and gonostyli. 64 Thorax and legs. 65 Mid tibial apical spines. 66 Abdominal segments 7–9 and spermathecae." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4425573" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4425573/files/figure.png" pageId="30" pageNumber="459">Figs. 61–66</figureCitation>
