<subSubSection id="91F4650B280FFFA6FF4CF8EDFAC5F822" pageId="31" pageNumber="460" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="D9513680280FFFA6FF4CF8EDFAC5F822" blockId="31.[151,1437,151,1977]" pageId="31" pageNumber="460">
<emphasis id="EB9AEA92280FFFA6FF4CF8EDFE89F8D7" bold="true" box="[199,332,1842,1868]" pageId="31" pageNumber="460">Discussion.</emphasis>
The type locality of this new species is located on the southern 
<collectingRegion id="1B2AF862280FFFA6FB91F8ECFB42F8D6" box="[1050,1159,1843,1869]" country="United States of America" name="Maryland" pageId="31" pageNumber="460">Maryland</collectingRegion>
portion of the Delmarva Peninsula (Outer Coastal Plain), where both males and two females were collected with Malaise traps. However, the other three female 
<typeStatus id="06558822280FFFA6FEE5F8A4FE1CF80E" box="[366,473,1915,1941]" pageId="31" pageNumber="460">paratypes</typeStatus>
were collected west of the Chesapeake Bay (Inner Coastal Plain). This suggests that this species also likely inhabits 
<collectingRegion id="1B2AF862280FFFA6FE72F840FDA1F822" box="[505,612,1951,1977]" country="United States of America" name="Delaware" pageId="31" pageNumber="460">Delaware</collectingRegion>
and 
<collectingRegion id="1B2AF862280FFFA6FD11F840FD30F822" box="[666,757,1951,1977]" country="United States of America" name="Virginia" pageId="31" pageNumber="460">Virginia</collectingRegion>
and possibly other nearby mid-Atlantic states.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
